  "name": "RPlog_A_Meeting_with_Paro",
  "title": "A Meeting with Paro",
  "summary": "Aboard the Imperial Star Destroyer Tormentor, the Sith zealot Simon Sezirok seeks an audience with Vorn Paro, the cold and calculating Director of the Imperial Security Bureau, to demand the release of his loyal captive Mailyn Raines. Simon argues that Mailyn is uniquely valuable as bait to lure the Jedi in numbers rather than be executed, while Paro -- a master manipulator who reveals that he secretly orchestrated Simon's rise and tracks the movements of Aurejin and Jessalyn -- tests Simon's resolve before granting his request. In an unprecedented act of amnesty, Paro releases Mailyn into Simon's custody, but only after maneuvering Simon, through a careful emotional gauntlet, into an alliance: their shared devotion to Order and to the Emperor binds them, and Paro offers the reach of the ISB in exchange for Simon's reports and service. Simon, wary of the hooks in Paro's words but bound first to his True Source and his crusade against the Jedi, accepts, and the two seal their pact with a handshake before Paro departs.",
